.\\n\\n**Analyzing library dependencies**\\n\\nI’m looking into a library jar that has no debug information. I’m considering whether I can add a dependency to include source lines, but that may not help because the active class is still unknown. If I add a newer dependency, it might help with line numbers. However, if the dependency still lacks debug info, I'm unsure if coverage improves. I'm curious if adding dependencies impacts behavior and source lines since version mismatches could complicate things further.\\n\\n**Considering test dependency options**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether it’s allowed to add a test dependency correctly. The json-smart package embeds the ASM package, which complicates things because adding org.ow2.asm might mask those embedded classes. That doesn’t seem ideal. I also thought about using an explicit test source class, but shadow classes in real packages aren’t allowed. It’s tricky! I’m wondering if I could modify the build.gradle for JaCoCo to include classes without source, but reports need line numbers, which is another challenge.\\n\\n**Inspecting dynamic-access files**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether dynamic access is referring to a raw report that's more about static scanning of a native image report instead of runtime stack. It seems like I need to take a closer look at dynamic-access files to really understand what's going on here. This might clarify some of the concepts I'm trying to grasp, so it's worth diving into those files. Let's see what insights I can find!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_045e736fd1a3faba016a0eae6506dc8190a894320d2403845e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqDq51-vtQWjTaaE8cSyTaQXVLy8bmjbBDFMVEac-dP3-wXijtFLsD92Xns6I1pZRYI9TLg7wakQVpgSTvCjz-ELvT5Y6Z0gJGRnECrTmdb9U0R2B7eOOZWWV_GoyacBEc1hjeP0_UcL-3RG_mNMm4Ez4ZMibMG18RCzjIDn8mEpmPIh0-dtD9ntvjwLt17FHskJQDJVcjtgbeSgLhdXUeU3lj-mr-jZF5Rd7palf-_yWr_AtGKTD7a3Xs-OeHH9r6TD3X_nl2isXL1iH5fiGnkKun6x061sHXAkEHeNBQa8aEikQzW