{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_61","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `net.minidev:json-smart:2.2`, but it left behind a preserved branch with a candidate fix:\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7378-fails-javac-compile-net.minidev-json-smart-2.2-2dda0f51\n\nThe original failing stage was `compileTestJava`: the first failing run shows `CollectionMapperInnerMapTypeTest.java` still importing `net.minidev.json.mapper.AMapper` and `net.minidev.json.mapper.Mapper`, which do not exist in `json-smart:2.2` (`forge/logs/net.minidev:json-smart:2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-21T06-44-07-929266Z.log`). After that, the automation spent several iterations on native-image test failures, first a `NullPointerException` from `DefaultMapperCollection` (`forge/logs/net.minidev:json-smart:2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-21T06-44-50-778069Z.log`), then a `ClassReaderTest` failure with `java.io.IOException: Class not found` (`forge/logs/net.minidev:json-smart:2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-21T07-09-09-081893Z.log`).\n\nThe confusing part is that the preserved branch now appears healthy: `stats/net.minidev/json-smart/2.2/execution-metrics.json` records the generation strategy as `success` after 10 iterations, ending at commit `127685c1e52a996bbd3e6694649d32f8b5652a64`, and the final local validation logs all pass, including `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-21T07-15-10-029336Z.log`, `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-21T07-15-09-561589Z.log`, and `logs/checkstyle/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-21T07-15-39-684066Z.log`. This looks more like a job/orchestration failure after the patch converged than a still-reproducible repo validation failure.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `tests/src/net.minidev/json-smart/2.2/` and `metadata/net.minidev/json-smart/2.2/`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=net.minidev:json-smart:2.2` from the preserved branch to confirm the final pass is reproducible.\n3. If that passes, open a manual fix PR from the preserved branch; if not, continue from the native-test failure logs above."}}
